President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate three key leaders for his administration. Shailen P. Bhatt is nominated for Administrator of the Federal Highway Administration at the U.S. Department of Transportation. Bhatt has a background in transportation innovation and has held leadership positions at the Colorado Department of Transportation, Delaware Department of Transportation, and the U.S. Department of Transportation. He has also been involved in various transportation organizations and advisory boards.

Jeff Marootian is nominated for Assistant Secretary for Energy Efficiency and Renewable Energy at the U.S. Department of Energy. Marootian currently serves as a Special Assistant to the President and has previously worked in the Washington D.C. government and the Obama-Biden Administration. He has experience in sustainable transportation technologies and infrastructure projects.

Stephen A. Owens is nominated for Chairman of the Chemical Safety and Hazard Investigation Board. Owens is currently a member of the U.S. Chemical Safety and Hazard Investigation Board and has a background in environmental law and regulation. He has previously served in the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency and the Arizona Department of Environmental Quality.

These nominations demonstrate President Biden's focus on transportation, energy efficiency, renewable energy, and chemical safety in his administration.